According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Electronic Nose Market was valued at USD 39.3 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 42.3 million in 2025 to USD 64.9 million by 2032, registering a CAGR of 7.6% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady expansion due to rising demand for rapid quality control in the food & beverage and pharmaceutical industries, stringent safety and environmental regulations, and continuous advancements in sensor technologies and artificial intelligence. The increasing availability of compact and portable electronic nose systems is further supporting adoption across industrial, healthcare, and environmental applications.
